## đź”µ Special Character Filenames

| Situation | Problem | Fix | Example |
|---|---|---|---|
| Filename starts with `-` | Read as a flag | Use `./` prefix | `cat ./-file` |
| Filename starts with `--` | Read as a flag | Use `./` prefix | `cat ./--file` |
| Filename has spaces | Terminal splits it | Use quotes or `\` | `cat ./"my file"` |
| Filename has hyphens + spaces | Both problems | Use `./` + quotes | `cat ./"--my file"` |
| Filename starts with `~` | Read as home dir | Use `./` prefix | `cat ./~file` |
| Filename starts with `$` | Read as variable | Use `./` prefix | `cat ./$file` |
| Filename starts with `!` | Triggers history expansion | Use `./` prefix | `cat ./!file` |
| Filename starts with `...` | No problem | No fix needed | `cat ...filename` |

